article.headline: Starks scores 20 to carry CS Northridge past Seattle 76-65
article.linkText: Starks scores 20 to carry CS Northridge past Seattle 76-65
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- — TJ Starks scored 20 points and Cal State Northridge beat Seattle 76-65 on Monday. Lance Coleman II had 13 points for Cal State Northridge (2-1) and Amound Anderson added 12. Darius Brown II had eight assists, moving into seventh on the school career list, passing Troy Brown, who had 316 assists from 1984-88. Darrion Trammell scored a career-high 25 points for the Redhawks (3-1). Riley Grigsby added 18 points and eight rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
